100:〔Takumi〕“N-Nanami, we need to talk.”\p;
200:〔Nanami〕“Huh? What about?”\p;
300:Without looking up from the manga she was reading, she gave an apathetic reply.\n;She'd been flipping through various volumes from the piles of manga stacked up in the corner of the room.\p;
400:〔Takumi〕“I-It's serious, so actually listen...”\p;
500:〔Nanami〕“Wh-What's the matter? Weird for you to get so serious all of a sudden.”\p;
600:Perplexed, she closed the manga, straightened her back, then faced me.\p;
700:〔Nanami〕“Ready when you are.”\p;
800:〔Takumi〕“...Do you remember a-anything about the day before yesterday?”\p;
900:The day before yesterday, Nanami had been cowering outside my container house, completely naked.\p;
1000:Her clothes, school bag, and bangle were all missing.\n;As for her phone, it'd been sent to me in a cardboard box, covered in blood.\p;
1100:Nothing about this was normal.\p;
1200:Nanami had said herself that not even she knew what'd happened.\n;She'd been suffering from mild amnesia.\p;
1300:Was she still dealing with it, though? Maybe she'd recovered since then.\n;After all, she was acting like she was totally back to her usual self...\p;
1400:When I asked her if she remembered anything now, Nanami immediately frowned, then lightly shook her head from side to side.\p;
1500:〔Nanami〕“Still the same...”\p;
1600:〔Takumi〕“Seriously...? N-Nothing at all...?”\p;
1700:〔Nanami〕“Seriously. Nothing at all.”\p;
1800:〔Nanami〕“Yeah, I've been trying as hard as I can to just not think about it. I haven't even told Mom...”\p;
1900:〔Nanami〕“Thanks to that, it was pretty tough dodging the question of where exactly my uniform went... Hehe...”\p;
2000:Hm, maybe I should take her to the hospital after all.\n;What field of study would amnesia even fall under? Psychiatry?\p;
