2200:At least, that was my thought process... until I remembered Dr. Takashina had been murdered as a part of New Gen.\n;A sharp pain shot deep into my chest.\p;
2300:〔Takumi〕“Nanami... M-My... life is in danger...”\p;
2400:〔Nanami〕“Huh?”\p;
2500:Nanami's eyes went wide.\p;
2600:Of course, pretty much anyone would react like that if I suddenly said something so batshit.\p;
2700:Problem was, the batshit stuff was the truth.\n;So, I decided to tell her everything.\p;
2800:I told her about “Shogun.” About how I'd witnessed the third New Gen case, the Cruc-affixion, and how after that, countless strange, terrifying things had been following me without end.\p;
2900:I told her about the threatening e-mails and other messages “Shogun” had sent me right before she'd landed naked on my doorstep. And lastly, I told her about the two prank calls I'd received from a fake version of her.\p;
3000:At first, Nanami forced a smile and said, “Big Bro? Don't you think you're being kinda delusional?”\n;But eventually, she realized that I wasn't joking around, and her expression stiffened.\p;
3100:〔Takumi〕“Listen, n-no more going out a-alone for a while.”\p;
3200:〔Takumi〕“We could be attacked at any moment...”\p;
3300:〔Nanami〕“B-Big Bro... You're scaring me...”\p;
3400:〔Takumi〕“I-I'm scared too...”\p;
3500:〔Takumi〕“Th-That's why we need to stick together.”\p;
3600:If the two of us stuck together, we could keep each other safe.\p;
3700:Not that I had any clue how a shitty older brother like me could keep her safe, nor how I'd support her feelings and whatnot. All I knew was that I couldn't bear it if she left me alone.\p;
3800:I would've preferred help from someone who could've offered physical protection, but...\n;Well, my first choice would've been the police, but I was hesitant to talk to them.\p;
3900:Those detectives I'd spoken to in front of the KURENAI Conference Hall hadn't shown themselves since then. What'd happened to all that talk of defending me?\p;
4000:Besides, they still might've suspected me of being the culprit behind the Cruc-affixion.\n;Trusting the police was out of the question.\p;
4100:Until I could think of a better countermeasure, the only choice I had was to stay locked in my base.\p;
4200:Sinking into the couch, Nanami wrapped her arms around herself, and simply trembled.\p;
